# Security Checklist

Source: GENERAL_CLAUDE.md § Security Checklist.

Run before every release. Every unchecked item is a release blocker.

## Authentication (when auth exists)

- [ ] Asymmetric signing for access tokens in production
- [ ] Access tokens ≤15 minutes
- [ ] HTTP-only secure refresh tokens
- [ ] Refresh rotation enabled
- [ ] Reuse revokes family/session
- [ ] Passwords: adaptive hash ≥bcrypt-12 equivalent
- [ ] MFA secrets encrypted at rest
- [ ] Account lockout after failed logins

## API (when HTTP API exists)

- [ ] Auth middleware on protected endpoints
- [ ] Rate limiting on all endpoints
- [ ] Schema validation on request bodies
- [ ] CORS restricted to known origins
- [ ] Security headers via middleware/gateway
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs
- [ ] No stack traces in production errors
- [ ] Parameterized queries via ORM

## Infrastructure

- [ ] Non-root containers (when used)
- [ ] Secrets in env/secret store, not source
- [ ] Dependency audit clean at policy level
- [ ] Pinned images/runtimes
- [ ] Database not public without auth
- [ ] Cache/broker password protected
